title: (x) Eat Well - Swinkydad {Lisa}
content:
my teacher asked me if i could find out what font this is.. i have searched for a while to no avail.. can anyone help? (EAT WELL)   
   
 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20071104014502im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/messages/83/19848.jpg)

 [‹ Before 1950 elegant serif](http://web.archive.org/web/20071104014502/http:/www.typophile.com/node/1878 "Go to previous forum topic") [ZedaSoft logo font is unknown ›](http://web.archive.org/web/20071104014502/http:/www.typophile.com/node/1976 "Go to next forum topic")
author: vwcruisn

comments.content:
Haven't got a clue, Jason. As the lc 'a' and 'e' are   
flipped versions of the same peculiar shape, there's   
a possibility this is tailor made or at least customized.

gather together all the unsolved fontidentifications and give to your teacher.. fair enough... huh?!   
   
an i for an i

Take a look at [Swinkydad](http://web.archive.org/web/20071104014502/http:/www.fontalicious.com/super/fonts.html). You have to browse through a couple pages of fonts to find it at the site. The lc e is wrong, but Yves may be right about flipping the 'a'.
You are totally welcome. I am just delighted when I actually recognize something on this board.

Jason, meet Lisa P, our secret weapon for locating hard-   
to-find freeware fonts. Nice ID, Lisa!
